messages.subject: LoTR
messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 9/25/02 11:00:12 AM Central Daylight Time, AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com writes:
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 9/25/02 11:00:12 AM Central Daylight Time,
AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com writes:

<< I really enjoyed the movie, but I'm sorry and curious about why they
didn't
say that it was Frodo's birthday too, and his thirty-third, his coming of
age. They just talk about Bilbo's birthday, but the really cool thing about
that party was it was eleventy-leven for Bilbo AND 33rd for Frodo, right? >>

Yes, AND...they left out my favorite character......Tom Bombadil!!! Wah.
And the fact that Frodo left Bag End NINE years after Gandalf left, not days
later.
And all the cool stuff between Bag End and the new house...and the
BarrowWraiths....
'tis the facts of a book being made into a movie.
